node.Title: Blockchain Selection
node.Description: (Main Model)

node.Title: Functional appropriateness
node.Description: degree to which the functions facilitate the accomplishment of specified tasks and objectives

node.Title: Functional completeness
node.Description: degree to which the set of functions covers all the specified tasks and user objectives

node.Title: Functional correctness
node.Description: degree to which a product or system provides the correct results with the needed degree of precision

node.Title: Functional suitability
node.Description: degree to which a product or system provides functions that meet stated and implied needs when used under specified conditions

node.Title: Reliability
node.Description: degree to which a system, product or component performs specified functions under specified conditions for a specified period

node.Title: Performance efficiency
node.Description: performance relative to the amount of resources used under stated conditions

node.Title: Usability
node.Description: degree to which a product or system can be used by specified users to achieve specified goals with effectiveness, efficiency and satisfaction in a specified context of use

node.Title: Maintainability
node.Description: degree of effectiveness and efficiency with which a product or system can be modified by the intended maintainers

node.Title: Security
node.Description: degree to which a product or system protects information and data so that persons or other products or systems have the degree of data access appropriate to their types and levels of authorization

node.Title: Compatibility
node.Description: degree to which a product, system or component can exchange information with other products, systems or components, and/or perform its required functions, while sharing the same hardware or software environment

node.Title: Portability
node.Description: degree of effectiveness and efficiency with which a system, product or component can be transferred from one hardware, software or other operational or usage environment to another

node.Title: Supplier
node.Description: Description about anyone who provides goods or services to a company or individuals.

node.Title: Cost
node.Description: Denotes the amount of money that a company spends on the creation or production of goods or services.

node.Title: Product
node.Description: Description about any article or substance that is manufactured or refined for sale.

node.Title: Maturity
node.Description: degree to which a system, product or component meets needs for reliability under normal operation

node.Title: Availability
node.Description: degree to which a system, product or component is operational and accessible when required for use

node.Title: Fault tolerance
node.Description: degree to which a system, product or component operates as intended despite the presence of hardware or software faults

node.Title: Recoverability
node.Description: degree to which, in the event of an interruption or a failure, a product or system can recover the data directly affected and re-establish the desired state of the system

node.Title: Time behavior
node.Description: degree to which the response and processing times and throughput rates of a product or system, when performing its functions, meet requirements

node.Title: Resource utilization
node.Description: degree to which the amounts and types of resources used by a product or system, when performing its functions, meet requirements

node.Title: Capacity
node.Description: degree to which the maximum limits of a product or system parameter meet requirements

node.Title: Appropriateness recognizability
node.Description: degree to which users can recognize whether a product or system is appropriate for their needs

node.Title: Learnability
node.Description: degree to which a product or system can be used by specified users to achieve specified goals of learning to use the product or system with effectiveness, efficiency, freedom from risk and satisfaction in a specified context of use

node.Title: Operability
node.Description: degree to which a product or system has attributes that make it easy to operate and control

node.Title: User error protection
node.Description: degree to which a system protects users against making errors

node.Title: User interface aesthetics
node.Description: degree to which a user interface enables pleasing and satisfying interaction for the user

node.Title: Accessibility
node.Description: degree to which a product or system can be used by people with the widest range of characteristics and capabilities to achieve a specified goal in a specified context of use

node.Title: Modularity
node.Description: degree to which a system or computer program is composed of discrete components such that a change to one component has minimal impact on other components

node.Title: Reusability
node.Description: degree to which an asset can be used in more than one system, or in building other assets

node.Title: Analyzability
node.Description: degree of effectiveness and efficiency with which it is possible to assess the impact on a product or system of an intended change to one or more of its parts, or to diagnose a product for deficiencies or causes of failures, or to identify parts to be modified

node.Title: Modifiability
node.Description: degree to which a product or system can be effectively and efficiently modified without introducing defects or degrading existing product quality

node.Title: Testability
node.Description: degree of effectiveness and efficiency with which test criteria can be established for a system, product or component and tests can be performed to determine whether those criteria have been met

node.Title: Confidentiality
node.Description: degree to which a product or system ensures that data are accessible only to those authorized to have access

node.Title: Integrity
node.Description: degree to which a system, product or component prevents unauthorized access to, or modification of, computer programs or data

node.Title: Non-repudiation
node.Description: degree to which actions or events can be proven to have taken place, so that the events or actions cannot be repudiated later

node.Title: Accountability
node.Description: degree to which the actions of an entity can be traced uniquely to the entity

node.Title: Authenticity
node.Description: degree to which the identity of a subject or resource can be proved to be the one claimed

node.Title: Co-existence
node.Description: degree to which a product can perform its required functions efficiently while sharing a common environment and resources with other products, without detrimental impact on any other product

node.Title: Interoperability
node.Description: degree to which two or more systems, products or components can exchange information and use the information that has been exchanged

node.Title: Adaptability
node.Description: degree to which a product or system can effectively and efficiently be adapted for different or evolving hardware, software or other operational or usage environments

node.Title: Installability
node.Description: degree of effectiveness and efficiency with which a product or system can be successfully installed and/or uninstalled in a specified environment

node.Title: Replaceability
node.Description: degree to which a product can replace another specified software product for the same purpose in the same environment

node.Title: Organizational structure
node.Description: Description of the organizational structure of the supplier company.

node.Title: Positioning and Strength
node.Description: Description of the position of the supplier company in the market.

node.Title: Reputation
node.Description: Capability of the supplier to perform similar projects based on past experiences and certifications.

node.Title: Services Offered
node.Description: Description of the services offered by the supplier.

node.Title: Support
node.Description: Description of the support mechanisms offered by the supplier.

node.Title: Licensing Schema
node.Description: Description of the COTS component licensing options.

node.Title: Licensing Costs
node.Description: Detail of the costs for the different licensing options

node.Title: Platform Cost
node.Description: Estimation of the cost for the required production platform

node.Title: Implementation Cost
node.Description: Estimation of implementation costs based on similar past experiences.

node.Title: Network Cost
node.Description: Estimation of additional cost for network operation.

node.Title: Stability
node.Description: Attributes of the product that bear on the stability of the product.

node.Title: Ownership
node.Description: Attributes in relation to the intellectual property rights.

node.Title: Deliverables
node.Description: Detail of the out of the box and post implementation deliverables.

node.Title: Parameterization / Customization
node.Description: Attributes in relation to the initial effort required for the product to operate.

node.Title: Guarantees
node.Description: Detail of the guarantees provided over the product.

node.Title: (d)App Token
node.Description: A token that is implemented on the application level on top of a blockchain (with underlying protocols)

node.Title: .NET
node.Description: This platform support the development of new applications/tokens/contracts/blockchains in the .NET programming language

node.Title: Application Layer
node.Description: The blockchain has a layer on which (decentralized) applications can be developed and run

node.Title: Asset-backed Token
node.Description: Digital equivelant to physical assets - these token-types are claims on an underlying asset along with certain rights and obligations

node.Title: Atomic-swaps
node.Description: Exchange of assets between different blockchains based on hash-time locked contracts

node.Title: C++
node.Description: This platform support the development of new applications/tokens/contracts/blockchains in the C++ programming language

node.Title: Consensus Mechanism
node.Description: Allows for the secure updating of a state on a blockchain according to some specific state transition rules - where the right to perform the state transitions is distributed among the economic set

node.Title: Cross-chain interoperable
node.Description: Different blockchains are interoperable with eachother with respect to exchanging assets/communicating

node.Title: Cross-Fault Tolerance
node.Description: BFT variant with the assumption of a powerful adversary that can control the message delivery schedule in the network besides the byzantine fault machines

node.Title: Cryptocurrency (legal status)
node.Description: The legal status of this token is that it acts as a store of value and medium of exchange which is not emitted by a central authority

node.Title: Cryptocurrency (purpose)
node.Description: The purpose of the token is to be a cryptocurrency - characterised by functioning as a global medium of exchange and store of value

node.Title: Cryptographic Tokens
node.Description: The blockchain has a token or coin which represents value (and is used) within the network or supports the creation of new (types of) tokens

node.Title: delegated Byzantine Fault Tolerance
node.Description: Variant of pBFT concensus mechanism - queries a random delegated node in the network about the state of the network until >66% of the network agree.

node.Title: Delegated Proof-of-Stake
node.Description: A variant of Proof-of-Stake in which nodes in the network elect delegates to create new blocks and verify the current state of the network - same incentive mechanisms as Proof-of-Stake

node.Title: Directed Acyclic graph
node.Description: Data structure which is a finite directed graph with no dorected cycles that consists of finitely many vertices and edges. Alternative to blockchain data structure

node.Title: Enterprise system integration
node.Description: The blockchain possesses characteristics which enable integration with current enterprise systems

node.Title: Federated Byzantine Agreement
node.Description: A round based voting mechanism in which (a group of) participants in the network know eachother and vote accordingly to other trusted nodes

node.Title: Golang
node.Description: This platform support the development of new applications/tokens/contracts/blockchains in the Golang programming language

node.Title: Hard-fork resistant
node.Description: Whether the blockchain can 'split' into different forks or not (blockchains) along with possible changes to the underlying protocol (Example: Bitcoin Core and Bitcoin Cash)

node.Title: Hybrid Token
node.Description: A token who's utility includes traits of both usage and work tokens

node.Title: Innovation
node.Description: The innovation going on for a blockchain platform relative to other platforms

node.Title: Instant transaction Finality
node.Description: Once a transaction is completed that transaction is completed directly for good and there is no way that the system can ever go back and revert that transaction

node.Title: Interoperability technologies
node.Description: This blockchain utilizes atleast one (including niche) mainly interoperability related feature

node.Title: Investment Token
node.Description: A token which purpose is that it's primarily intended as a way to invest in the issiung entity or underlying asset

node.Title: Java
node.Description: This platform support the development of new applications/tokens/contracts/blockchains in the Java programming language

node.Title: JavaScript
node.Description: This platform support the development of new applications/tokens/contracts/blockchains in the JavaScript programming language

node.Title: Legal Status (token type)
node.Description: The token(s) on this blockchain platform can be classified under a clear legal status

node.Title: Native Token
node.Description: A token that is implemented on the protocol-level of a blockchain and which is part of the blockchain's incentive mechanism

node.Title: Network Layer
node.Description: The layer on which the different nodes run the blockchain protocol and keep the records of transactions

node.Title: Network Token
node.Description: The intended purpose of this token to be used within a specific system (network - application - etc.)

node.Title: Network Value token
node.Description: The underlying value of these tokens is tied to the value and development of the underlying network

node.Title: Non-native Protocol Token
node.Description: A token that is implemented in a cryptoeconomic protocol on top of a base-protocol

node.Title: Off-chain State-Channels
node.Description: Transactions can be performed on a local network (off-chain) and integrated with the main blockchain by sending the results of these transactions

node.Title: On-chain transactions
node.Description: The transactions of the network are executed on the main blockchain

node.Title: Permissioned
node.Description: In this type of blockchain participants in the network have different authorization with respect to performing operations in the network

node.Title: Permissionless
node.Description: In this type of blockchain all participant in the network are authorized to perform the same operations

node.Title: Plasma-chains
node.Description: A series of smart contracts which creates hierarchical trees of sidechains (with it's own set of rules and constraints) which relays information back to the main chain periodically

node.Title: Popularity in the market
node.Description: The popularity of a blockchain platform relative to other platforms

node.Title: practical Byzantine Fault Tolerance
node.Description: A concensus mechanism designed to be Byzantine Fault Tolerant and fairly easy to use

node.Title: Privacy Technologies
node.Description: This blockchain utilizes atleast one (including niche) mainly privacy related feature

node.Title: Private
node.Description: In this type of blockchain only users that are authenticated can participate in the network

node.Title: Programming Language Support
node.Description: The blockchain supports at least one programming language to create new applications/contracts/tokens/blockchains

node.Title: Proof-of-Authority
node.Description: Proof of Authority (PoA) is a modified form of Proof of Stake (PoS) where instead of stake with the monetary value - a validators identity performs the role of stake

node.Title: Proof-of-Elapsed Time
node.Description: A consensus-mechanism with random leader election verified within a Trusted Ececution Environment (e.g. Intel SGX)

node.Title: Proof-of-Stake
node.Description: A concensus-mechanism based on weighed voting of nodes with a stake in the network on the state of the network - incentivized by rewarding rightful voters and penalizing dishonest voters.

node.Title: Proof-of-Work
node.Description: A concensus-mechanism based on solving cryptographic puzzles -reward for solving puzzle given to first miner who solves the puzzle

node.Title: Protocol Layer
node.Description: The blockchain has it's own 'base' protocol layer which among other things defines the consensus mechanism

node.Title: Public
node.Description: In this type of blockchain no authentication is needed for participating as a node in the consensus process in addition to writing and reading transactions in the network

node.Title: Purpose (token type)
node.Description: The token(s) on this blockchain platform serves a clear purpose

node.Title: Python
node.Description: This platform support the development of new applications/tokens/contracts/blockchains in the Python programming language

node.Title: Quantum-computing resistant
node.Description: Whether the blockchain's public-keys are cryptographic resistant to quantum computing

node.Title: Resilience Technologies
node.Description: This blockchain utilizes atleast one (including niche) mainly resilience related feature

node.Title: Ring-signatures
node.Description: Makes it possible to specify a set of possible signers of a transaction without revealing which member actually produced the signature

node.Title: Scalability Technologies
node.Description: This blockchain utilizes atleast one (including niche) mainly scalability related feature

node.Title: Security Token
node.Description: The legal status of this token is that it showcases security-like features like voting on decisins regarding the issuing entity - dividends or profit shares

node.Title: Sharding
node.Description: Sharding allows nodes and transactions to be divided into smaller groups and nodes only need to store certain segments of the blockchain rather than the main-chain of transactions

node.Title: Share-like Token
node.Description: The underlying value of these tokens is based on a share in the succes of the issuing entity (e.g. yields - profit-shares)

node.Title: Side-chains
node.Description: Independent chains that utilize the main-chain protocol but allow for additional changes without impacting the main-chain. Enables transfer of assets between multiple blockchains and off-chain transactions

node.Title: SIEVE
node.Description: SIEVE consensus mechanism is a BFT protocol designed to handle non-determinism in chaincode execution - filters out diverging transaction-outcomes

node.Title: Smart-contracts
node.Description: Programmed contracts that are enforced by computer protocols which enable transactions -in this domain on a blockchain

node.Title: SNARKS
node.Description: Variant of zero-knowledge proofs in which no interaction is necessary between prover and verifier

node.Title: Solidity
node.Description: This platform support the development of new applications/tokens/contracts/blockchains in the Solidity programming language

node.Title: Spam-attack resistant
node.Description: To which degree the blockchain is resistant to a high amount of transactions which have the purpose of clogging the network

node.Title: Sybil atack resistant
node.Description: The blockchain is made cryptographic resistant against attack where a majority of the nodes in the network are controlled by a single entity without the rest of the network knowing this

node.Title: Technical Layer (token type)
node.Description: The token(s) on this blockchain platform has a underlying value

node.Title: Technology Maturity
node.Description: The maturity of a blockchain platform relative to other platforms

node.Title: Transaction Speed
node.Description: The transaction speed of a blockchain platform relative to other platforms

node.Title: Turing Complete
node.Description: The Virtual Machine that is used by the blockchain platform is Turing Complete

node.Title: Underlying value (token type)
node.Description: The token(s) on this blockchain platform has a underlying value

node.Title: Usage Token
node.Description: The utility this token provides is access to a digital service (similar to a paid API key)

node.Title: Utility (token type)
node.Description: The token(s) on this blockchain platform provides a certain utility

node.Title: Utility Token
node.Description: The legal status of this token is that it provides a clearly defined utility within a network or application

node.Title: Virtual Machine
node.Description: The Blockchain platform utilizes a Virtual Machine to run the smart contracts

node.Title: Work Token
node.Description: The utility this token provides is the right to contribute to a system

node.Title: Zero-knowledge Proof
node.Description: A cryptographic method in which one party (prover) assures another party (verifier) that they have knowledge of value X without revealing the actual value
